review_title: Not the thick durable wildwood bibs but great for lighter work
reviews: Nice lightweight, good for lighter work. Ordered these by accident thinking they were thicker, but ended up keeping them. If you are looking for thicker, durable overalls, go for the wildwood overalls. If you need something for yard work, these are good
This hat kept my head warm nicely but irritated my forehead. I bought it for work and couldn’t wear it two days in a row because my forehead was sore. It’s freat for short term wear

These seats were great and do their job well! Until you lean back too hard. The side straps do give quite a bit if you lean back too hard. They also loosen over the course of your sit. They’re great for the price, though! Makes watching hockey in the town arena a lot more comfortable
Lots of valuable info. Lots of filler pages, which were definitely unnecessary but the book is super useful!

This journal is awesome for planning and productivity! It guides you through every step of mapping out your goals so that you actually achieve them. I am so impressed and will definitely keep buying this journal.
